-- Yen Falls After Bank of Japan Expands Asset Purchases to Support Economy
-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 2012-02-14T03:50:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/yen-falls-after-bank-of-japan-expands-asset-purchases-to-support-economy.html
The yen fall after the  Bank of Japan (8301) 
said it expanded its asset-purchase fund to ensure a recovery.
The yen dropped as much as 0.2 percent to 77.76 per dollar,
before trading at 77.68 at 12:48 p.m. Tokyo time from 77.57
yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
